{
    "title": "JSON:Presenter",
    "description": "A demo presentation that outlines the features of JSON:Presenter",
    "aspectW": 16,
    "aspectH": 9,
    "container": {
        "border": "1px solid black",
        "background": "black"
    },
    "defaults": {
        "fontFace": "Times New Roman,serif",
        "fontSize": 40,
        "fontWeight": "normal",
        "fontStyle": "normal",
        "fontColor": "white",
        "textAlign": "left",
        "blockLeft" : 0,
        "blockTop" : 0,
        "blockBackground" : "none",
        "blockBorder": "none",
        "blockPaddingLeft": "1em",
        "blockPaddingTop": "0"
    },
    "blocks": {
        "title 1": {
            "type": "text",
            "spec": {
                "blockTop": 300,
                "blockWidth": 1000,
                "blockHeight": 300,
                "textAlign": "center",
                "fontFace": "Helvetica,sans-serif",
                "fontSize": 200,
                "fontWeight": "bold"
            }
        },
        "title 2": {
            "type": "text",
            "spec": {
                "blockWidth": 1000,
                "blockHeight": 150,
                "textAlign": "center",
                "fontFace": "Helvetica,sans-serif",
                "fontSize": 100,
                "fontWeight": "bold",
                "blockPaddingTop": "1em"
            }
        },
        "body": {
            "type": "text",
            "spec": {
                "blockTop": 200,
                "blockWidth": 1000,
                "blockHeight": 800,
                "blockPaddingLeft": "8em",
                "blockPaddingTop": "4em"
            }
        }
    },
    "content":  {
        "presenter title": "JSON:Presenter",
        "slide 1": [
            "JSON:Presenter<sup>&copy;</sup> is a presentation format using JSON, that lets you create presentations that run in a web browser. Presentations can be similar to those created using PowerPoint or they can be considerably more elaborate, with extensive animation and sound.",
            
            "Presentations can run from any host, including static; all you need is one CDN-hosted JavaScript file and you're good to go.",
            
            "The JSON:Presenter<sup>&copy;</sup> engine is pure JavaScript. It can be used with any JavaScript framework, or with none."
        ]
    },
    "steps": [
        {
            "comment": "-------------------- Create the title and body blocks",
            "action": "create",
            "blocks": [
                "title 1",
                "title 2",
                "body"
            ]
        },
        {
            "comment": "---------------------------------- Set up the content",
            "action": "set content",
            "blocks": [
                {
                    "block": "title 1",
                    "content": "presenter title"
                },
                {
                    "block": "title 2",
                    "content": "presenter title"
                },
                {
                    "block": "body",
                    "content": "slide 1"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "comment": "------------------------------- Pause before we start",
            "action": "hold",
            "duration": 2
        },
        {
            "comment": "----------------------------------- Fade up the title",
            "action": "fade up",
            "blocks": "title 1",
            "duration": 3,
            "wait": true
        },
        {
            "comment": "---------------------------------- Hold for 4 seconds",
            "action": "hold",
            "duration": 4
        },
        {
            "comment": "--------------------------------- Fade down the title",
            "action": "fade down",
            "blocks": "title 1",
            "duration": 1
        },
        {
            "comment": "-------------------------- Fade up the title and body",
            "action": "fade up",
            "blocks": [
                "title 2",
                "body"
            ],
            "duration": 1,
            "wait": true
        },
        {
            "comment": "--------------------------------- Hold for 10 seconds",
            "action": "hold",
            "duration": 10
        }
    ]
}
